Contagious products are cool. The iPod was successful partly because it was the first cool Mp3 player. Contagious products are effective or excellent at what they do. The TiVo, for example, became an iconic digital video recorder because it allowed you to record your favorite TV shows so effortlessly. Contagious products are distinctive, or noticeably different from the competition. Consider the Hummer, for example – you wouldn’t confuse it with any other car.